{
  "purpose": "Day-7 POWER-UP of the Day-6 retrospective external validation. Expands the scored gene universe (44 -> 277) and the external truth set under a PRE-REGISTERED, label-blind membership rule, to test whether the calibrated gate's advantage over function-blind baselines converts from MARGINAL (iter4) to a CLEAN WIN or fails honestly.",
  "claim_under_test": "The calibrated gate's blinded GO/WITHHOLD adjudication (Claude free-text biological synthesis from ONLY {symbol, OT-T1D-assoc, eQTL n_sig}) ranks genes backed by INDEPENDENT real-world therapeutic evidence (approved/clinical drug targets for a fixed autoimmune indication list) ABOVE function-blind baselines (OT-assoc-alone, eQTL-count-alone, random), with the gate-minus-best-baseline 95% CI EXCLUDING 0.",
  "gate_definition": "IDENTICAL to Day-6/Check-A: blinded prompt gives ONLY gene symbol, OT-T1D genetic-association score, and CD4/Treg cis-eQTL n_sig; Claude returns GO:YES/NO. Reproduced here via host.llm (project rule: pasted API key NOT used). Reasoning-class model.",
  "membership_rule_LABEL_BLIND": {
    "text": "A gene is a CANDIDATE iff: perturbed in the Marson CD4 Perturb-seq sgRNA library AND NOT in the T1D gold set or any program-axis gene list AND ( it ranks in the top 120 of Open Targets T1D genetic-association among perturbed non-forbidden genes OR it ranks in the top 200 of Open Targets autoimmune-disease (MONDO_0007179) overall association among perturbed non-forbidden genes ). Uses ONLY objective OT rankings + perturbation membership; NO drug/clinical-trial/label information enters the rule.",
    "K_t1d": 120,
    "K_autoimmune": 200,
    "perturbed_source": "data/raw/sgrna_library_metadata.suppl_table.csv target_gene_name",
    "forbidden": "t1d_gold_set.json genes + axes_manifest.json all-axes pos/neg + treg dropped-in-gold"
  },
